amendatorysection.para:
(1)
Provide English reading and writing and math skills required to succeed in
a postsecondary educational credentialing or degree program;

(2)
Lead to the attainment of college credit and a recognized postsecondary educational
credential or an industry-recognized credential;

(3) Be open only
to low-income participants who are co-enrolled in adult education, developmental
education, or English as a second language;

(4) Target the specific workforce needs
of an occupational sector within the state and provide services aimed at improving
education, skills, and employment prospects for low-income adults;
